44 ///
45 /// \class AttributeCommon
46 /// The AttributeCommon class implements data common to all DICOS attributes.
47 /// Tag, representation, multiplicity, and ID.
48 ///
49 class AttributeCommon
50 {
51 public:
52  ///
53  /// Default constructor.
54  /// Tag is (0xFFFF, 0xFFFF)
55  /// Multiplicity is 0, ID is 0
56  ///
57  AttributeCommon();
58  virtual ~AttributeCommon();
59 
60  ///
61  /// Construct an attribute with a tag, Value Representation and multiplicity.
62  /// Attribute ID is set to 0.
63  ///
64  AttributeCommon(const Tag &tag);
65 
66  ///
67  /// Copy Constructor
68  ///
69  AttributeCommon(const AttributeCommon &attribute);
70 
71  ///
72  /// Assignment operator
73  ///
74  AttributeCommon& operator=(const AttributeCommon& attribute);
75 
76  /// Stream insertion operator
77  friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const AttributeCommon&);
78 
79  ///
80  /// Reset to default values
81  ///
82  virtual void FreeMemory();
83 
84  ///
85  /// Comparison operator
86  ///
87  bool operator==(const AttributeCommon& attribute)const;
88 
89  ///
90  /// Comparison operator
91  ///
92  bool operator!=(const AttributeCommon& attribute)const;
93 
94  ///
95  /// Set DICOS Tag
96  ///
97  virtual bool SetTag(const Tag& tag);
98 
99  /// Set the DICOS Tag to the given Group and Element.
100  /// Note: This method does not check if the (Group, Element)
101  /// pair is valid for the attribute type.
102  virtual bool SetTag(const S_UINT16 nGroup, const S_UINT16 nElement);
103 
104  ///
105  /// Get DICOS Tag
106  ///
107  const Tag& GetTag()const;
108 
109  /// Set the Group and Element to 0xFFFF to invalidate the Attribute.
110  virtual void ClearTag();
111 
112  ///
113  /// Get Value Representation
114  /// Implement by derived attribute class that must know their own VR.
115  ///
116  virtual DcsString GetVR()const = 0;
117 
118  ///
119  /// Get Value Multiplicity
120  /// Derived attributes must know and report their multiplicity
121  ///
122  virtual S_UINT32 GetVM()const = 0;
123 
124  ///
125  /// Get the Attribute's Data Size in bytes
126  /// Derived attributes must know and report the size of their data.
127  ///
128  virtual S_UINT64 GetSizeInBytes()const = 0;
129 
130  /// Check that the Tag group and element are not 0xFFFF.
131  bool TagIsValid() const;
132 
133  ///
134  /// Write the Attribute Common data to the indicated file
135  ///
136  /// @param file File to read from
137  /// @param errorlog Error log
138  /// @param bExplicit Value Representation (VR) is explicitly encoded.
139  ///
140  virtual bool Write(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const bool bExplicit) const;
141 
142  ///
143  /// Read the Attribute Common data from the indicated file
144  ///
145  /// @param file File to read from
146  /// @param errorlog Error log
147  /// @param bExplicit VR is explicitly encoded instead of determined from Tag.
148  /// @param strVR Value Representation if it is explicitly given
149  /// @param attributemanager Attribute manager
150  ///
151  virtual bool Read(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const bool bExplicit, DcsString &strVR, const AttributeManager &attributemanager);
152 
153  ///
154  /// Read VR and set to the provided tag
155  ///
156  /// @param file File to read from
157  /// @param errorlog Error log
158  /// @param tag Tag to set to this attribute
159  /// @param strVR Output VR
160  /// @param bExplicit Explicit encoding flag
161  /// @param attributemanager Attribute Manager
162  ///
163  virtual bool Read(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const Tag &tag, DcsString &strVR, const bool bExplicit, const AttributeManager &attributemanager);
164 
165  /// Check the Attribute's value is valid for its VR.
166  /// @return true/false false if the Tag is invalid
167  virtual bool IsValid() const;
168 
169 protected:
170  inline void Verify() const; ///< Check that the implementation pointer is valid
171 
172  class ImplAttributeCommon;
173  ImplAttributeCommon *m_pImplAttributeCommon; ///< Internal implementation
174 
175  bool Read_internal(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, DcsString &strVR, const bool bExplicit, const AttributeManager &attributemanager);
176 
177 };

182 /// \class AttributeHeader

185 class AttributeHeader : public AttributeCommon

189  /// Initialize with default values

197 
198  ///
199  /// Destructor
200  ///
201  virtual ~AttributeHeader();
202 
203  ///
204  /// Copy operator
205  ///
206  AttributeHeader& operator=(const AttributeHeader &attrib);
207 
208  using AttributeCommon::Read; // Bring in AttributeCommon Read/Write to avoid hiding overloaded functions
209 
210  ///
211  /// Read the group, element, and VR
212  ///
213  /// @param file File to read from
214  /// @param errorlog Error log
215  /// @param bExplicit Explicit encoding flag
216  /// @param strVR Output attribute VR
217  /// @param attributemanager Attribute Manager
218  ///
219  virtual bool Read(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const bool bExplicit, DcsString &strVR, const AttributeManager &attributemanager);
220 
221  ///
222  /// Read the group, element, and VR
223  ///
224  /// @param file File to read from
225  /// @param errorlog Error log
226  /// @param bExplicit Explicit encoding flag
227  /// @param attributemanager Attribute Manager
228  ///
229  bool Read(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const bool bExplicit, const AttributeManager &attributemanager);
230 
231  ///
232  /// Read VR and set to the provided tag
233  ///
234  /// @param file File to read from
235  /// @param errorlog Error log
236  /// @param tag Tag to set to this attribute
237  /// @param bExplicit Explicit encoding flag
238  /// @param attributemanager Attribute Manager
239  ///
240  bool Read(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const Tag &tag, const bool bExplicit, const AttributeManager &attributemanager);
241 
242  ///
243  /// Get Value Representation
244  ///
245  virtual DcsString GetVR()const;
246 
247  ///
248  /// This class does not have a VM. Returns 0.
249  ///
250  virtual S_UINT32 GetVM()const;
251 
252 protected:
253  class ImplAttributeHeader;
254  ImplAttributeHeader *m_pImplAttributeHeader; ///< Internal implementation
255 
256  ///
257  /// Disabled
258  ///
259  virtual S_UINT64 GetSizeInBytes()const;
260 
261  ///
262  /// Disabled
263  ///
264  virtual bool Write(IFile &file, ErrorLog &errorlog, const bool bExplicit) const;
265 };

3155  /// Provide a memory manager responsible for allocating pixel data slices to the read process.
3156  /// This provides a way of managing memory allocation and deallocation of pixel data.
3157  ///
3158  /// During the read process, if this SDK needs to allocate a slice it will call IMemoryManager::Allocate()
3159  /// instead of allocating the memory internally. When this SDK needs to deallocate the slice it
3160  /// will call IMemoryManager::Deallocate() instead of deleting it internally.
3161  ///
3162  /// For pixel data with more than 1 sample per pixel or voxel:
3163  /// If using planar configuration 0: Slices are allocated with size (bytes) = WIDTH * HEIGHT * NUM_SAMPLES * SIZE_OF_TYPE.
3164  /// This allocates all samples per slice.
3165  /// If using planar configuration 1: Slices are allocated with size (bytes) = WIDTH * HEIGHT * SIZE_OF_TYPE.
3166  /// This allocates a slice for each sample (i.e. For RGB: a slice for R samples, a slice for G samples, and a slice for B samples)
3167  ///
3168  /// SIZE_OF_TYPE = The size of the pixel data's type, such as S_UINT8, S_UINT16, etc.
3169  ///
3170  /// \ref IMemoryManager
3171  void SetPixelDataMemoryManager(IMemoryManager *pMemManager);
3172  /// @see SetPixelDataMemoryManager
